value.0: Hello. I can see that you've rudely intruded upon my home. What is that you want?
Farewell indeed.

I am Wanev, a man well-versed in the magical arts and of no small renown. I am somewhat displeased at your presence here, but I can see that you are quite capable, seeing that you are still alive. My idiot friends will have many a jest at my expense.
Well, if you wish to get yourself killed, why should I care?

I've been experimenting with summoning a lesser demons and testing their obedience. So, I thought it wise to summon an imp and make him do the legwork. Two birds with one stone. There was, uh, a bit of a setback.

value.0: Know this: if you should be able to close the demon portal, I would be most grateful. You need only kill the imp that I originally summoned. That should take care of the portal. Do so and I will come up with a suitable reward.
Good luck.

Hmph. No doubt you have plundered and looted. You intrude upon my humble abode, and you have the audacity to ask for more? I suppose I can humour you for your boldness. Perhaps we can help each other.

I've been experimenting with summoning a lesser demons and testing their obedience. I was somewhat less than careful with the preparations and the little fiend escaped the summoning circle. Let this be a lesson about casting when drunk.
You've already done the job for me. There is nothing else I require from you for now. So, you'd best take your leave now, as I have a lot of important work to do.
Off with you.
I suppose I can arrange that. I'll not be responsible for whatever happens in there.
